The paper discusses the application of Deep Learning and Deep Belief Networks (DBN) for medical examination data and cancer prediction. This falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the adaptive structural learning method for DBN, which involves the generation-annihilation algorithm, which falls under the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also mentions the use of C4.5 for knowledge extraction, which is a decision tree algorithm and falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Databases (cs.DB).
